# W1: Introduction {#w1-introduction .unnumbered}

## Definition of law {#definition-of-law .unnumbered}

Law is the body of rules of conduct with binding legal force and effect,
which are prescribed, recognized and enforced by a controlling authority
(predominantly the law-making authority).

Types: civil, common, muslim, customary and mixed system law.

### Civil law

-   codification; French & German legal tradition

-   written law as the main source of law

### Common law

-   judge-made law; former British colonies, US, UK

-   case-by-case reasoning of decisions

-   case law as the main source of law

### Functions of law {#functions-of-law .unnumbered}

1.  Avoiding conflicts - substantive law; rights, obligations and
    > prohibitions

2.  Resolving conflicts - procedural law; procedures by which rights,
    > obligations and prohibitions can be enforced

