### **Reproachable guilt** {#reproachable-guilt .unnumbered}

#### Intent (dolus)

a)  willful intent (purpose)

b)  acting in the awareness of a high degree of probability

> → 'foreseeable consequences' (inevitable side effects)

c)  recklessness: dolus eventualis

-   knowing and willing exposure to a considerable chance; Hoornse
    > pie-judgment

Example: 'assault / battery' Art. 300, 'murder' Art. 289, 'manslaughter'
Art. 287

#### Negligence (culpa)

a)  conscious negligence (knows but naive)

b)  unconscious negligence (careless or thoughtless)

Example: 'culpable homicide' Art. 307 PC or Art. 6 Road Traffic Act →
Porsche judgment

### **Defenses** {#defenses .unnumbered}

