1.  Cancel contract (revoke offer)

-   Supreme Court: Lindeboom - Municipality of Amsterdam (1969); 'the
    > party who makes his offer irrevocable deprives himself of the
    > opportunity to prevent the contract being concluded by the
    > acceptance of the offer within the time limit'

-   6:219 DCC: regret ≠ mistake or vitiated consent!

2.  Cancel contract (hindsight)

-   Supreme Court: Silver cup of Stevensweert (1960); 'one who
    > relinquishes ownership of his item in exchange for an agreed
    > counter-performance thereby forfeits the chance that the item may
    > later prove to have characteristics he was unaware of at the time
    > of sale'

